I think this may be a little before November 1931 ... see below:

&quot;In 1931 the Port Jackson Steamship Company constructed an enormous enclosed shark-proof bathing area in Manly Cove, adjacent to the ferry wharf. It opened in December 1931. The pool and its distinctive play equipment of pontoons, slides and treadmills was designed and built by the company’s workforce at Kurraba Point. It was described at the time as “the finest swimming pool in Australia”, superior to anything the other Sydney beach resorts could offer.&quot;

